# Amazon FSx

## What is Amazon FSx?

Amazon FSx is a fully managed file storage service provided by AWS. It offers high-performance file systems optimized for specific workloads and operating systems.

## Types of Amazon FSx

* Amazon FSx for Windows File Server
* Amazon FSx for Lustre
* Amazon FSx for NetApp ONTAP
* Amazon FSx for OpenZFS

## Features

* Fully managed service
* High performance
* Highly available
* Supports Windows and Linux workloads
* Automatically managed by AWS

## Advantages

* Easy deployment
* High-speed file access
* Reliable and scalable
* Optimized for enterprise applications

## Use Cases

* Windows applications
* High Performance Computing (HPC)
* Machine Learning
* Media processing
* Enterprise file storage

## Real Life Example

A company runs a Windows-based application that requires a shared file system. Instead of managing its own file server, it uses Amazon FSx for Windows File Server to provide fast and reliable shared storage.

## Key Points

* FSx = Fully managed file system
* File Storage
* Optimized for specific workloads
* Supports Windows and Linux
* Managed by AWS
